tarquin@texas.net wrote:
> Symptoms: Popup menus completely hosing the system. No oops log, no
> keyboard, no process switching, complete lockup. Midis hang, mouse quits,
> keyboard quits. Occurs under UP 2.0.35, 2.0.36, and SMP 2.1.131ac9.
>
> XF86_S3V server: fvwm2 menus kill system
> XF86_SVGA server: fvwm2 survives, xemacs and netscape kill system
> turning on noaccel causes fvwm2 to break again.
>
> With a Cirrus Logic GD5430 card, X survives, but consumes ungodly amounts
> of CPU time and misbehaves when moving windows.
>
> I have not had the machine die or misbehave at the console, so this may be
> an X problem. However, the fact that the machine gets completely hosed
> without any error logging seems to suggest that it might be something
> deeper.
